BSE - Spain: OIE confirmation 20001123.2030
[1
Date: Tue 30 Jan 2001 13:16:52
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Australian Broadcast Corp., 30 Jan 2001 [edited
<http://www.abc.net.au/news/newslink/nat/newsnat-30jan2001-98.htm>

EU Proposes Tighter Beef Regulations After Mad Cow Scare
------------------------------------
European agriculture ministers meeting in Brussels have agreed to recommend
a complete ban on the sale of beef products using any part of the animal's
spinal cord. If adopted, the ban spells the end of the sale of popular cuts
of meat such as T-bone and rib eye steaks, which are already heavily
regulated. Sales have slumped by 27 per cent across Europe, which has led
to difficulties in disposing of thousands of tons of unwanted meat.
The Finnish agriculture minister, Carlavy Hemmiler, hopes the new measures
will be introduced across the European Union (EU). "Our conclusions
[results? are very good, we are going to continue this message," the
minister said. "Now the most important thing is that all the member states
must implement all these measures."
